<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I think it would be fun to work in some sort o=
f middle management role=C2=A0at a big public company and also be friends w=
ith a big scary activist investor. Everyone would have to walk=C2=A0on eggs=
hells around you just a bit, and if you ever=C2=A0disagreed with your boss,=
 or if your boss tried to demote you or fire you for something that you did=
, you could call up your activist buddy to run a proxy fight to get the who=
le board and=C2=A0management team replaced. =E2=80=9CI was not happy with m=
y bonus this year so I had my friend take over the company and fire everyon=
e.=E2=80=9D Just a weird dynamic.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/30562430.279853/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL=
2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDEtMTAvY3J5cHRvLWJhbmtzLW93ZS10aGVtc2VsdmVzLW1vbmV5P2Nt=
cGlkPUJCRDAyMTUyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXd=
zbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDIxNSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4=
b8524a319a23cB4f526ec1" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" targ=
et=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bo=
rder-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: =
solid; background-color: #ccc;"> talk sometimes</a> about the odd governanc=
e dynamics of corporate chief executive officers who are also controlling s=
hareholders: Technically the CEO works for the board, and the board can fir=
e the CEO, but the board works for the shareholders, and the shareholder-CE=
O can fire the board. There is a standoff; the corporate hierarchy circles =
back on itself. This would be like that but weirder. You work for your boss=
 who works for the CEO who works for the board who works for the shareholde=
rs who work for you.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You don=E2=80=99t see a ton of it,=C2=A0but he=
re is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30562430.279=
853/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9ob3ctbmVsc29uLXBlbHR6LWFuZC1kaXN=
uZXlzLW1hcnZlbC1jaGllZi10ZWFtZWQtdXAtaW4tcHJveHktZmlnaHQtZmNiMTYwMmY_bW9kPW=
hwX2xpc3RhX3BvczM/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB6687d236" itemprop=3D"StoryLink"=
 itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-de=
coration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #=
000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">a Wall Street =
Journal story</a> that is a little like that:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Longtime friends Isaac =E2=80=9CIke=E2=80=9D P=
erlmutter and activist investor Nelson Peltz shared a similar opinion: Walt=
 Disney Co. was spending too much money.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Mr. Perlmutter, chairman of Disney=E2=80=99s M=
arvel Entertainment unit, was known to be passionate about cost-cutting and=
 once demanded that an action sequence in the 2008 movie =E2=80=9CIron Man=
=E2=80=9D be shot with only three Humvees, instead of the 10 called for in =
the script. His feuds with Robert Iger during the chief executive=E2=80=99s=
 first tenure over how to run Marvel=E2=80=99s movie studio caused a rift t=
hat remains.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Meanwhile, Mr. Perlmutter supported Mr. Peltz =
and his campaign to get onto Disney=E2=80=99s board and push for significan=
t changes to Disney=E2=80=99s governance and operations, including cost cut=
s. Mr. Peltz ended that campaign Thursday after Mr. Iger announced plans to=
 remove 7,000 jobs and reduce spending by $5.5 billion as part of a reorgan=
ization plan.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Though Disney didn=E2=80=99t respond to all of=
 Mr. Peltz=E2=80=99s demands, the commitment to austerity pleased both him =
and Mr. Perlmutter. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Messrs. Iger and Perlmutter have had a tense r=
elationship since 2015, when Mr. Perlmutter=E2=80=99s quarrels with current=
 Marvel Studios chief Kevin Feige over budgets and movie slates grew so int=
ense that Mr. Iger, then in his first stint as Disney=E2=80=99s CEO, interv=
ened and removed Mr. Perlmutter as CEO of Marvel=E2=80=99s movie studio, ac=
cording to people familiar with the matter. Mr. Iger later stripped Mr. Per=
lmutter of further responsibilities, including control over Marvel=E2=80=99=
s television shows, heightening the acrimony between them, these people sai=
d.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Is the story here that Iger, the CEO, demoted =
Perlmutter, the head of a division, so Perlmutter called in an activist sha=
reholder to cut Iger down to size? I mean, no, but a little bit? Disney=E2=
=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30562430.2=
79853/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE3NDQ0ODkvMDAwM=
TE5MzEyNTIzMDI1NzY2L2QzNTQ1NjVkZGVmYzE0YS5odG0jdG9jMzU0NTY1Xzg/607f07ceef4b=
8524a319a23cBd42257f7" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" targe=
t=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bor=
der-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: s=
olid; background-color: #ccc;"> proxy statement for the Peltz proxy fight</=
a>, filed last week, does=C2=A0<em>begin=C2=A0</em>the story with Perlmutte=
r, =E2=80=9Can employee and shareholder of the Company,=E2=80=9D bringing i=
n Peltz to support Disney=E2=80=99s previous CEO, Bob Chapek.=C2=A0Actually=
 the paragraph is worth quoting in full:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Early in the summer of 2022, Isaac=
 Perlmutter, an employee and shareholder of the Company, who currently serv=
es as Chairman of Marvel Entertainment, and previously served as Chief Exec=
utive Officer of Marvel, called Bob Chapek, then the Chief Executive Office=
r of the Company, to urge Mr. Chapek to meet with Nelson Peltz, the Chief E=
xecutive Officer of Trian Management. Mr. Chapek noted that he had business=
 travel coming up in Paris, France, and thus his schedule near term would n=
ot work. Mr. Perlmutter responded that Mr. Peltz was vacationing on his yac=
ht somewhere off the coast of France and so geography would not be an imped=
iment. Mr. Perlmutter told Mr. Chapek he should have a =E2=80=9Cfriendly lu=
nch=E2=80=9D with Mr. Peltz in France and it would be a good investment of =
his time. Mr. Perlmutter=E2=80=99s assistant worked with Mr. Chapek=E2=80=
=99s office and Mr. Peltz=E2=80=99s office to organize the meeting over a l=
unch.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CHey Bob would you like to meet with a=
 famous activist investor?=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9COooh I=E2=80=99d love to, real=
ly I would,=C2=A0but I=E2=80=99m gonna be in France, sorry, <em>quel dommag=
e</em>.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9CThat=E2=80=99s okay, he=E2=80=99s on a yacht some=
where off France, he can come to you.=E2=80=9D Imagine being the law firm a=
ssociate writing that paragraph at midnight in your office. Sounds nice!</p=
>
