<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The basic proposition of crypto shadow banks l=
ike Celsius Network Ltd. was:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You deposit your crypto with Celsius.<=
/li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Celsius pays you some very high in=
terest rate on your crypto, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.=
com/click/30562430.279853/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljb=
GVzLzIwMjItMDEtMjcvY2Vsc2l1cy1zLTE4LXlpZWxkcy1vbi1jcnlwdG8tYXJlLXRlbXB0aW5n=
LWFuZC1kcmF3aW5nLXNjcnV0aW55P2NtcGlkPUJCRDAyMTUyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWR=
pdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDIxNSZ1dG1fY2FtcG=
FpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB7ce249f3" itemprop=3D"StoryLi=
nk" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text=
-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color=
: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  as much a=
s 18%</a>, and uses your crypto to make risky bets.</li>=09<li style=3D"mar=
gin-bottom: 5px;">Celsius loses the money, can=E2=80=99t give you back your=
 crypto, and goes bankrupt.</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I mean, that is not literally the proposition =
that Celsius <em>advertised</em>, but (1) it=E2=80=99s what happened and (2=
) it's=C2=A0<em>kind of=C2=A0</em>what it advertised? Like, if you are fina=
ncially literate, an 18% interest rate on a demand deposit account does=C2=
=A0<em>mean=C2=A0</em>that they=E2=80=99re going to lose your money?=C2=A0=
=E2=80=9CEither the bank is lying or Celsius is lying,=E2=80=9D Celsius pro=
moter Alex Mashinsky <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cli=
ck/30562430.279853/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIw=
MjItMDEtMjcvY2Vsc2l1cy1zLTE4LXlpZWxkcy1vbi1jcnlwdG8tYXJlLXRlbXB0aW5nLWFuZC1=
kcmF3aW5nLXNjcnV0aW55P2NtcGlkPUJCRDAyMTUyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW=
1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDIxNSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249b=
W9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC7ce249f3" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" ite=
mscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decora=
tion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0000=
00; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  famously said</a=
>, so you had a 50/50 shot of getting it right.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway, there is an obvious problem with this =
proposition, which is that Celsius loses your money and you don=E2=80=99t g=
et it back. But there is also another, slightly less obvious problem, which=
 is that Celsius pays you 18% interest. The problem is that=C2=A0you owe ta=
xes on that interest, which you can=E2=80=99t pay, because Celsius lost you=
r money. Bloomberg=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/30562430.279853/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGlj=
bGVzLzIwMjMtMDItMTUvYmFua3J1cHQtY3J5cHRvLWxlbmRlcnMtaGl0LWludmVzdG9ycy13aXR=
oLXRheC1iaWxscy1mb3ItZnJvemVuLWZ1bmRzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAyMTUyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJn=
V0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDIxNSZ1d=
G1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB3e72ed0f" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
  Claire Ballentine reports</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Interest earned on bank accounts, certificates=
 of deposit and corporate bonds is subject to income tax in the year it=E2=
=80=99s generated, according to the Internal Revenue Service. Typically, th=
at=E2=80=99s a fairly straightforward process: Banks and other institutions=
 send out 1099 forms listing the taxpayer=E2=80=99s interest income, which =
is then used when determining overall obligations for tax season. =C2=A0</p=
>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But in a quirk of last year=E2=80=99s crypto c=
ollapse, investors are now receiving tax bills for money locked up on platf=
orms like Celsius and Voyager Digital, which have frozen customer withdrawa=
ls as they undergo bankruptcy proceedings.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It could hardly come at a worse time for crypt=
o investors. Not only have digital asset prices plunged in the wake of FTX=
=E2=80=99s collapse, but inflation, high housing costs and rising interest =
rates are also making it more difficult for everyday people to afford regul=
ar expenses =E2=80=94 let alone taxes on investments they=E2=80=99ve likely=
 lost.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Paying 18% interest into your account, and the=
n not letting you withdraw the money from the account, ends up giving you n=
egative cash flow; you=E2=80=99d have been better off without the interest.=
=C2=A0In <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30562430.=
279853/aHR0cHM6Ly9uZXdzLmJsb29tYmVyZ2xhdy5jb20vYmFua3J1cHRjeS1sYXcvQ2Vsc2l1=
cy1EZWJ0b3JzLVByb3Bvc2UtTm92YVd1bGYtYXMtQnV5ZXItaW4tU2FsZS1QbGFu/607f07ceef=
4b8524a319a23cB08365544" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" tar=
get=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; b=
order-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style:=
 solid; background-color: #ccc;">
other Celsius news</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Celsius Network Ltd=C2=A0has proposed a plan t=
hat calls for most users to recover the majority of their assets and allows=
=C2=A0NovaWulf Digital Management=C2=A0to manage a restructured version of =
the bankrupt crypto lender.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The proposal calls for Celsius users with less=
 than $5,000 of crypto tied up in interest-bearing accounts to receive a 70=
% recovery in the form of liquid digital assets like Bitcoin and Ethereum,=
=C2=A0court papers=C2=A0show. Those smaller accounts make up most of Celsiu=
s=E2=80=99s interest-bearing account holders.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Bigger account holders will receive tokenized =
shares of post-bankruptcy Celsius and an unspecified amount of crypto, cour=
t papers show. The reborn company =E2=80=94 which will hold its crypto mini=
ng and illiquid assets =E2=80=94 =C2=A0will be managed by NovaWulf. =C2=A0<=
/p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">NovaWulf would inject as much as $55 million i=
nto the new company under the plan, according to court papers. Its incentiv=
es will be =E2=80=9Cclosely aligned=E2=80=9D with shareholders because of a=
 profit-sharing arrangement, Celsius advisers said in a slide deck. =E2=80=
=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The plan also calls for Celsius users to reap =
any benefits of a trust that will sue former Celsius insiders, according to=
 court papers.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Huge <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbus=
iness.com/click/30562430.279853/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9=
uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDItMTQvdGhyZWUtYXJyb3dzLWdpdmVzLWNyeXB0by1hbm90aGVyLX=
RyeT9jbXBpZD1CQkQwMjE1MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY=
2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzAyMTUmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f=
07ceef4b8524a319a23cBdd4e0a6a" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscop=
e" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !import=
ant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-=
style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  growth area</a> in crypto, really,=
 tokenizing the right to sue the people who made money in the last crypto b=
oom.</p>
